{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ところ}}

{{IPAfont|⟨to<sub>2</sub>ko<sub>2</sub>ro<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/tokoro/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=ところ|-}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>  Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' (c. 759 CE).<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|19|4288}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man19Yo.html#4288 here]</ref>

A surface analysis suggests that this could be an ancient compound of {{IPAfont|⟨to<sub>2</sub>}} (“place”, as in {{m|ja|跡}} {{IPAfont|⟨ato<sub>2</sub>⟩}}, “footprint, track”, from “foot '''place''', where one has stepped”) + {{IPAfont|⟨ko<sub>2</sub>⟩}} (noun-forming suffixing element denoting “place”, as in {{m|ja|ここ}} {{IPAfont|⟨ko<sub>2</sub>ko<sub>2</sub>⟩}}, “here”, from “this '''place'''”) + {{IPAfont|⟨ro<sub>2</sub>⟩}} (noun-forming suffixing element, apparently indicating within a general area, possibly as in {{m|ja|心}} {{IPAfont|⟨ko<sub>2</sub>ko<sub>2</sub>ro<sub>2</sub>⟩}}, “heart, mind, emotions”, {{m|ja|頃}} {{IPAfont|⟨ko<sub>2</sub>ro<sub>2</sub>⟩}}, “general span of time, around a certain time”、{{m|ja|うつろ}} {{IPAfont|⟨uturo<sub>2</sub>⟩}}, “hollowness, empty interior”).

{{ja-noun|ところ}}

# a [[place]], a [[scene]], a [[site]]; an [[address]]
#: {{ja-usex|遠い'''所'''に行ってみたい。|とおい '''ところ''' に いって みたい。|I want to go to a '''faraway''' place.}}
#: {{ja-usex|あの窓の'''ところ'''にいる人は誰？|あの まど の '''ところ''' に いる ひと は だれ？|Who is the person by that window?}}
#: {{ja-usex|嫌な'''ところ'''を直す|いや な '''ところ''' を なおす|to change the unpleasant '''part/aspect''' (of one's personality)}}
# a state of being
## {{lb|ja|after a plain verb}} [[about to]]
##: {{ja-usex|映%画を見に行く'''ところ'''だった。|えい%が を み に いく '''ところ''' だった。|I was '''about to''' go to a movie.}}
## {{lb|ja|after a verb in the past tense}} [[just]]
##: {{ja-usex|駅に着いた'''ところ'''です。|えき に ついた '''ところ''' です。|I '''just''' arrived at the station.}}
## {{lb|ja|after a verb in the progressive ている}} {{non-gloss definition|indicates the current state, or how you have progressed so far in a chain of actions}}
##: {{ja-usex|今、敬%語を勉%強している'''ところ'''です。|いま、けい%ご を べん%きょう して いる '''ところ''' です。|I'm now learning polite language.|ref=[https://detail.chiebukuro.yahoo.co.jp/qa/question_detail/q1442454474]}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|と}}

{{IPAfont|⟨to<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → {{IPAchar|/to/}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=と|-}}.  Appears mainly as an affixing element indicating place, as in {{m|ja|後||tr=ato|after; behind; the back of something}}, from {{m|ja|跡||tr=ato|footprint, track}}, itself a compound of {{m|ja|足||tr=a|foot}} + {{m|ja|所||tr=to|place}}; or in {{m|ja|留まる||tr=todomaru|to stop in a place}}.

In modern Japanese references,<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref> there are various compound terms ending in ''-to'' or ''-do'' that are spelled and / or described as deriving from this {{m|ja|所||tr=to|place}}, including {{m|ja|隈所||tr=kumato|a bent and twisted place, such as a tunnel, out of sight}}, {{m|ja|立ち所||tr=tachido|standing place}}, {{m|ja|竈||tr=kamado|kiln}}.  However, an historical analysis reveals that many of these terms do not derive from {{m|ja|所}}, {{m|ja|処}} {{IPAfont|⟨to<sub>2</sub>⟩}} “place”, but rather from {{m|ja|戸}}, {{m|ja|門}} {{IPAfont|⟨to<sub>1</sub>⟩}} “gate, door, place of entry and exit”.

{{der-top}}
* {{ja-r|後|あと}}: after; behind; the back of something
* {{ja-r|跡|あと}}: footprint, track; scar
* {{ja-r|留まる|とどまる}}: to stop in a place
* {{ja-r|留める|とどめる}}: to stop something in a place
{{der-bottom}}
